cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel acuity score framework that leverages temporal measurements and interpretable deep learning models to assess illness severity at any point during an ICU stay. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning models, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential impact of the proposed framework on shared decision-making processes among patients, providers, and families, which suggests that it could belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper focuses on predicting in-hospital mortality among critically ill patients, which suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
